Amma da karfe shida na safe, lokacin da Gegard Mousasi da Rory MacDonald za su hadu, masu kallo a Burtaniya sun yi mamaki lokacin da suka ga Peppa Pig.
Wasu ba su ji daɗi ba bayan sun yi awoyi da yawa suna jiran ganin yaƙin.
Wani mai sha'awar ya bayyana sauyawar zuwa waɗannan zane-zanen yara a kan Twitter a matsayin "wani abin ban dariya mara kyau".
"Dokar jihar ta ce wannan abun bai dace da karfe 6 na safe ba, don haka sai aka sauya zuwa shirye-shiryen yara", in ji Dave Schwartz, babban mataimakin shugaban kasuwanci da sadarwa na Bellator, lokacin da aka tambaye shi game da watsa shirye-shiryen.
"Peppa Pig, wannan shi ne".
Scott Coker, shugaban Bellator, ya ce za su yi la'akari da masu kallo na Burtaniya a shirye-shiryen su na gaba.
"Ina ganin za mu iya magance wannan idan muka yi tunanin maimaitawa", in ji Coker.
"Amma idan 6 na safe ne a can, ba za mu iya magance shi ba har sai ranar Lahadi, wanda zai zama Litinin a gare su.
Amma muna aiki don samun mafita.
Sa'ad da na soma wannan canjin, na soma samun saƙonni da yawa, kuma ba duka ba ne suke da kyau.
Mun yi kokarin gyara shi domin mun yi tunanin cewa kuskure ne na fasaha.
Amma a'a, matsalar gwamnati ce.
Na yi alkawari ba zai faru ba kuma.
Za mu yi wasa biyar maimakon shida, kuma muna so mu ba magoya bayanmu damar yin wasa, amma mun wuce gona da iri.
